article.headline: SE Louisiana 65, Southern 62
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Ricky Woods scored a season-high 28 points, including a pair of free throws with 10.6 seconds left, and Southeastern Louisiana University withstood a last-minute scoring barrage by Southern University to escape with a 65-62 win on Monday night. Leonard Harden added 10 points and 10 rebounds as Southeastern (4-1) kept Southern winless (0-6). Woods gave Southeastern a 61-50 lead with 1:45 remaining on a dunk off a steal by Scott Roniger. But the Jaguars began to close the gap. Ralph Hishaw made one of two free throws to close the deficit to 61-51 before Chris Alexander's three-point play with 58 seconds left got Southern to 61-54. After Jerrid Campbell rebounded a miss by Harden, Alvin Mott hit a 3-pointer with 33 seconds remaining to get Southern to within four, 63-59. Then DeForrest Riley-Smith's 3-pointer with 19 seconds left closed the gap to 63-62. On Southeastern's next possession, Woods was fouled by Alexander and he made both free throws to give the Lions a 65-62 lead. Southern drove the ball down the floor but a potential game-tying 3-pointer by Alexander was off the mark and Woods grabbed the rebound to seal the win. Alexander led Southern with 17 points, while Hishaw added 15. Southeastern led at the half, 35-20.
